<TITLE> Bay depression stationary </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Apr 28 (bdnews24.com)  The depression over the southwest Bay of Bengal and adjoining southeast Bay remained practically stationary, a special weather bulletin issued Monday said. The depression was centred at 6 am Monday 1290 kms south west of Chittagong port, 1220 kms south west of Cox's Bazar port and 1180 kms south-southwest of Mongla Port. It is likely to intensity further and move in a northwesterly direction. Maximum sustained wind speed within 48 kms of the depression centre is about 50 km per hour, rising to 60 km per hour in gusts/squalls. The sea will remain moderate over the north Bay and rough near the depression centre. Maritime ports of Chittagong, Cox's Bazar and Mongla have been asked to keep hoisted distant cautionary signal number 1. All fishing boats and trawlers plying in the north Bay and in deep sea have been asked to stay near the coast until further order. bd
